{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TUBqEUuAuKKgyyFHjGQJBW","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d92c7bcb-37ff-4aa2-841f-ece7fabef071","uuid":"eec4b2f1-7b88-4f3e-9784-953bd011e96b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T12:29:20.875Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"## Session 7 — Started 2026-03-21T12:24Z","newString":"## Session 7 — Started 2026-03-21T12:24Z\n\n### 7-3-create-dockerfile — create-story (2026-03-21T12:27Z)\n\n- **Existing stub overwritten:** Prior `7-3-create-dockerfile.md` was auto-generated by `codeharness audit --fix`, titled \"Story 6-3\" with minimal ACs. Replaced entirely.\n- **Risk: AC3/AC4 require Docker daemon** — tagged integration-required. Cannot verify in environments without Docker.\n- **Risk: USER node in Dockerfile** — container runs as non-root, may fail if codeharness writes to root-owned paths.\n- **Observation:** Final story in final epic. Completing this closes the sprint.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n\n### 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates — verify (2026-03-21T07:55Z)\n\n- **Bug found and fixed:** `parseRalphStatus()` in `migration.ts` was missing the new `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by this story. Migration test was failing. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n- **Observability gap:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all `codeharness progress` CLI invocations. The progress command doesn't emit structured logs.\n\n### 0-2-ralph-progress-display — verify (2026-03-21T08:00Z)\n\n- **Proof format issue:** AC3 initially reused evidence from AC2 without its own `bash` code block, causing `codeharness verify` to report 3/4 ACs. Fixed by adding a distinct bash block.\n- **No BATS tests in container:** `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification relied on direct function invocation with mock data.\n- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** `_stream_id:*` pattern invalid for VictoriaLogs. Used `*` wildcard instead.\n\n### 0-3-run-command-dashboard — verify (2026-03-21T08:04Z)\n\n- **Minor format deviations:** Story specified checkmark/cross prefixes but implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent, passed verification.\n- **Architecture difference:** Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class but implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design.\n\n### 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver — verify (2026-03-21T08:09Z)\n\n- Clean verification — all 4 ACs passed without issues.\n\n### 0-5-2-stream-event-parser — verify (2026-03-21T10:35Z)\n\n- **Infrastructure fix:** `parseStreamLine` was not exported from `src/index.ts`, making it inaccessible in the container's dist bundle. Added re-export to `src/index.ts` and rebuilt.\n- **ESM import workaround:** Container requires `VITEST=1` env var to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import. Uses `node --input-type=module` for ESM.\n- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all parser invocations — `parseStreamLine` is a pure function with no telemetry.\n- **Non-standard status from previous session:** Sprint status had `verified` (not a valid status). Normalized to `verifying` before proceeding.\n- All 6 ACs passed black-box verification after infrastructure fix.\n\n---\n\n## Session 2 — Started 2026-03-21T10:44Z\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — create-story (2026-03-21T10:47Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity: No formal epic definition file for Epic 6.** Derived intent from story name, UX spec, and existing code.\n- **Workaround: Cost field source unclear.** Story assumes `result` events contain cost data — needs verification during implementation.\n- **Risk: AC10 snapshot test fragility.** Softened to \"matches spec format structure\" rather than literal character comparison.\n- **Observation:** Old `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework — stale/misleading.\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — dev-story (2026-03-21T10:56Z)\n\n- **Workaround: file split to avoid circular imports** — NFR9 300-line limit forced a 3-file split. `ink-app.tsx` composes `ink-components.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.tsx` to avoid circular deps. Adds indirection.\n- **Cost accumulation edge case** — `result` event cost only accumulates when `state.sprintInfo` is non-null. Cost from early events before sprint state init is lost.\n- **Iteration count delay** — `currentIterationCount` in run.ts is a mutable closure variable, updated from stderr parsing. Iteration count updates are delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n- **Missing artifacts** — AGENTS.md, exec-plan, and proof document not created (not in story tasks).\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Session 3 — Started 2026-03-21T11:04Z\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — verify (2026-03-21T11:05Z)\n\n- **Infrastructure:** Shared observability stack was already running but `codeharness status --check-docker` reported it as down. Port conflict when harness-specific compose tried to start — shared stack already bound ports. Resolved by using shared stack directly.\n- **Stale container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to `docker rm -f` before starting a new one.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync --story 6-1 --direction files-to-beads` failed with \"Story file not found or has no Status line\".\n- **Observation:** Verifier used static analysis of the dist bundle rather than runtime rendering. Valid black-box approach but doesn't test runtime behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Session 4 — Started 2026-03-21T11:14Z\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — create-story (2026-03-21T11:16Z)\n\n- **No epic-6 definition file exists.** Story file already existed with sufficient detail.\n- **Risk: AC5 requires manual verification** with screenshot proof — non-automatable, depends on having a valid story in backlog.\n- **Risk: AC1 references `ralph/logs/` for recorded NDJSON** — ephemeral/gitignored. Fixture needs hand-curation from real log.\n- **Observation:** Last story in Epic 6. Completing it closes the epic.\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — dev-story (2026-03-21T11:20Z)\n\n- **Test file location diverges from story spec**: Story specified `tests/run-pipeline.test.ts` but vitest root is `src/`. Placed at `src/__tests__/run-pipeline.test.ts`.\n- **No real recorded NDJSON logs available**: Fixture constructed synthetically — `ralph/logs/` only has single-line result events, not full stream-json output.\n- **makeLineHandler duplication**: Test reconstructs the handler because it's a closure in `run.ts`, not exported. Could diverge if `run.ts` changes.\n- **AC5 not completable autonomously**: Requires manual `codeharness run` and screenshot capture.\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — code-review (2026-03-21T11:26Z)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Test reimplemented production `makeLineHandler` instead of importing it — changes wouldn't be caught. Fixed by extracting `createLineProcessor` to `run-helpers.ts`.\n- **HIGH fixed:** Story File List wrong path. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** `makeLineHandler` not exportable (closure in run.ts). Extracted to run-helpers.ts.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Unused `vi` import.\n- **LOW unfixed:** No test for multi-byte UTF-8 split across chunk boundaries.\n- **LOW unfixed:** Renderer state accumulation test uses manual switch, not real Ink renderer.\n- **Coverage gap:** AC5 manual verification still incomplete.\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — verify (2026-03-21T11:33Z)\n\n- **Stale container from previous session:** Had to `docker rm -f codeharness-verify` before starting.\n- **Port conflict with shared stack:** `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to bind already-used ports. Used shared stack directly.\n- **AC5 genuinely escalated:** Requires human visual judgment of real-time Ink rendering — correctly tagged `integration-required` in story.\n- **All 4 automatable ACs passed** with 48 total assertions.\n\n### epic-6-retrospective (2026-03-21T11:37Z)\n\n- **Epic numbering collision:** Two sprints reused \"Epic 6\" for different epics. Stale retro file persisted across 4+ session retros before being overwritten.\n- **Action item carry-forward rate ~100%:** Retro action items are generated but never executed. Process failure, not documentation gap.\n- **Story 6-1 harder than expected:** NFR9 300-line limit forced 3-file split not anticipated during story creation.\n- **Story 6-2 harder than expected:** `makeLineHandler` was untestable closure — required production refactor to extract `createLineProcessor`.\n- **Known tech debt:** Cost accumulation data loss for events before `sprintInfo` init.\n\n---\n\n## Session 5 — Started 2026-03-21T11:42Z\n\n### 7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis — create-story (2026-03-21T11:43Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity: No formal Epic 7 definition exists.** Epic 7 only defined by story keys in sprint-status.yaml. No epic-level requirements in any planning artifact.\n- **Workaround: Existing story file overwritten.** The `audit --fix` command had previously generated a skeletal story. Replaced with proper story.\n- **Workaround: Sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent.** Harness-run process handled it.\n- **Risk: AC2 (fresh environment install) tagged integration-required** because verification container already has Semgrep pre-installed via Dockerfile.verify.\n- **Observation: Very small story.** ~10 lines in deps.ts plus test updates.\n\n### 7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis — dev-story (2026-03-21T11:49Z)\n\nNo issues reported. Clean implementation: 7 new tests, all 2920 tests passing.\n\n### 7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis — code-review (2026-03-21T11:53Z)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Missing test for CriticalDependencyError throw path. Added.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Semgrep test spec was duplicated instead of referencing registry. Fixed to use DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY.find().\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** AGENTS.md deps description omitted agent-browser.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Missing null-version branch coverage. Added two tests.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `skipped` status in DependencyResult is dead code. Pre-existing.\n- **LOW unfixed:** Semgrep fallback tests don't assert primary command attempted before fallback.\n- **LOW unfixed:** Unreachable nullish-coalescing branches (defensive code) preventing 100% branch coverage.\n\n### 7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis — verify (2026-03-21T12:00Z)\n\n- **Proof quality issue:** AC5 (unit tests) and AC6 (AGENTS.md) initially failed proof validation — attestation-only evidence without bash code blocks. Fixed by adding indirect CLI evidence.\n- **Stale container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to `docker rm -f` before starting.\n- **Shared stack detection issue recurs:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack running on all ports. Known recurring issue.\n- **Minor bug observed:** Audit gap descriptions show `undefined` instead of Semgrep rule message text. `parseSemgrepOutput` may not map `extra.message` correctly.\n- **Observability gap:** No log events from VictoriaLogs during verification (test project has no OTLP instrumentation).\n\n---\n\n## Session 6 — Started 2026-03-21T12:04Z\n\n### 7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests — create-story (2026-03-21T12:07Z)\n\n- **Existing story file had wrong title** (\"Story 6-2\") and was extremely thin. Overwrote entirely.\n- **Epic numbering collision:** Epic 7 in epics-overhaul.md is \"OpenSearch Backend\" but sprint-status.yaml's Epic 7 is \"Onboarding — Compliance Gaps\". Different epics, same number from different planning cycles.\n- **Risk: AC4 (fixing 14 skipped onboard.bats tests)** is the largest task with design ambiguity — tests broken because onboard.sh delegates to TS CLI.\n- **Risk: AC1 uses `brew install bats-core`** — macOS only. npm fallback (`bats` package) may not be 100% compatible with `bats-core`.\n- **Risk: AC7 (CI impact)** tagged integration-required — cannot verify locally.\n\n### 7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests — dev-story (2026-03-21T12:11Z)\n\n- **BATS not installed locally** — had to `brew install bats-core` during implementation. This is the exact gap the story addresses.\n- **No formal coverage report run** — all code paths exercised by tests but no formal coverage measurement.\n- **CI workflows unchanged** — kept manual BATS install in CI (intentional belt-and-suspenders with registry).\n\n### 7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests — code-review (2026-03-21T12:15Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** AGENTS.md deps.ts description missing \"BATS\" in the dependency list.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `deps.ts` branch coverage 89.28% — unreachable `??` null-coalescing fallback branches (dead defensive code).\n- **LOW unfixed:** `onboard.sh --help` is a single line, doesn't document `--json`/`--output` flags.\n- **Coverage:** 97.02% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor. deps.ts at 100% statements/functions/lines.\n\n### 7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests — verify (2026-03-21T12:20Z)\n\n- **4 ACs escalated:** AC2 (integration-required), AC4/AC5 (dev-time artifacts not in npm package), AC7 (integration-required). All genuinely impossible in black-box Docker.\n- **3 ACs passed:** Registry entry confirmed, bats installs and runs, audit no longer reports bats error.\n- **Shared stack detection issue recurs:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack running on all ports. Known recurring issue.\n- **Beads sync failed:** `bd` binary not found (ENOENT). Known — beads not installed.\n- **Observability gap:** No log events from VictoriaLogs during verification (test project has no OTLP instrumentation).\n\n---\n\n## Session 7 — Started 2026-03-21T12:24Z\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":178,"oldLines":3,"newStart":178,"newLines":10,"lines":[" ---"," "," ## Session 7 — Started 2026-03-21T12:24Z","+","+### 7-3-create-dockerfile — create-story (2026-03-21T12:27Z)","+","+- **Existing stub overwritten:** Prior `7-3-create-dockerfile.md` was auto-generated by `codeharness audit --fix`, titled \"Story 6-3\" with minimal ACs. Replaced entirely.","+- **Risk: AC3/AC4 require Docker daemon** — tagged integration-required. Cannot verify in environments without Docker.","+- **Risk: USER node in Dockerfile** — container runs as non-root, may fail if codeharness writes to root-owned paths.","+- **Observation:** Final story in final epic. Completing this closes the sprint."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
