{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YEN3iRRgC8DcyUnVcNETs4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here is a summary of what was done:\n\n**Created:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/Dockerfile` -- root Dockerfile for containerized deployment of the codeharness CLI tool.\n\n**Verified:**\n- All 6 dockerfile-validator rules pass: pinned FROM (node:22-slim), binary on PATH (npm install -g), verification tools (curl, jq on apt-get install line), no source copy, non-root USER (node), cache cleanup (rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*)\n- Full unit test suite: 2930 tests pass, 113 files, 0 regressions\n- `npm pack --dry-run` confirms root Dockerfile is excluded from npm package\n- No existing code was modified (only a new Dockerfile added)\n\n**Story file updated:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-3-create-dockerfile.md` -- status set to `review`, all tasks checked, Dev Agent Record / File List / Change Log added.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Workaround applied:** The `dockerfile-validator.ts` checks each line individually for the verification-tools rule (it looks for lines containing both `apt-get install` AND the tool name like `curl`/`jq`). A multiline Dockerfile with backslash continuation (`apt-get install -y \\` on one line, `curl \\` on the next) fails this check because no single line contains both the install command and the tool name. Worked around by putting `curl jq` on the same line as `apt-get install`. This is a limitation of the validator's line-by-line checking approach -- it doesn't handle Dockerfile line continuations. Not fixing the validator per story instructions (\"DO NOT Modify\").\n- **Integration tests not executed:** AC #3 and #4 (`docker build`, `docker run`) are marked `integration-required` and were not run in this session (requires Docker daemon and network access to pull base image). The Dockerfile follows the proven pattern from `templates/Dockerfile.verify`.\n- **Showboat proof document not created:** Left unchecked in verification requirements as it's a separate verification workflow artifact."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac1bb6281f60d4a26 (use SendMessage with to: 'ac1bb6281f60d4a26' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53186\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 163925</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d92c7bcb-37ff-4aa2-841f-ece7fabef071","uuid":"cca28f6e-72d2-4b66-a452-f1e389420dff","timestamp":"2026-03-21T12:32:22.930Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-3-create-dockerfile.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ac1bb6281f60d4a26","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here is a summary of what was done:\n\n**Created:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/Dockerfile` -- root Dockerfile for containerized deployment of the codeharness CLI tool.\n\n**Verified:**\n- All 6 dockerfile-validator rules pass: pinned FROM (node:22-slim), binary on PATH (npm install -g), verification tools (curl, jq on apt-get install line), no source copy, non-root USER (node), cache cleanup (rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*)\n- Full unit test suite: 2930 tests