{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SW1J7x4TLvUxM7w3q5rv5W","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-21\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n     4→**Session window:** ~04:21Z – ~04:45Z (approx 25 minutes)\n     5→**Sprint progress:** 15/20 stories done (75%), Epic 3 nearing completion\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 1. Session Summary\n    10→\n    11→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Phases Completed |\n    12→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|\n    13→| 3-3-onboard-alias | Epic 3: Audit Command | Verifying (all phases done, awaiting final verification) | create-story, dev-story, code-review |\n    14→\n    15→One story was attempted this session. It progressed through story creation, implementation, and code review without blocking failures. The story replaced a 478-line onboard command with a 40-line alias delegating to a shared audit handler — a 92% reduction in code.\n    16→\n    17→**Test results at session end:** 2783 tests passing across 119 files, 96.97% overall coverage, all files above 80% floor.\n    18→\n    19→---\n    20→\n    21→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    22→\n    23→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n    24→\n    25→- **Unsafe double type assertion** (HIGH) — `audit-action.ts:86` used `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` to bypass TypeScript type safety. Fixed during code review by using spread operator instead.\n    26→- **Dead branch guard** (MEDIUM) — `audit-action.ts:101` had a `fixStories &&` check that was always true at that point. Simplified to `else`.\n    27→\n    28→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n    29→\n    30→- **`console.log` in audit-action.ts:111** (LOW, not fixed) — The shared handler uses `console.log` directly instead of output utilities. Established codebase pattern but violates project conventions. Needs a new `raw()` output utility to fix properly. **Tracked as tech debt.**\n    31→- **`formatAuditJson()` is a pass-through no-op** (LOW, not fixed) — Exists for API symmetry with `formatAuditHuman()` but does nothing. Not harmful but adds a meaningless abstraction layer.\n    32→\n    33→### Code Quality Concerns\n    34→\n    35→- **NFR9 violation** — `onboard.test.ts` initially hit 325 lines (limit: 300). Compacted to 230 lines during code review. Shows that test file size estimates in story planning (100-150 lines) can be unreliable.\n    36→- **Branch coverage gap** — Missing test for `skipped: true` path in audit-action.ts. Added during code review, bringing branch coverage to 100%.\n    37→\n    38→### Verification Gaps\n    39→\n    40→- Story is in `verifying` status — final verification pass has not yet been completed as of session end.\n    41→\n    42→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n    43→\n    44→- None reported this session.\n    45→\n    46→### Planning/Ambiguity Issues\n    47→\n    48→- **Ambiguous AC3** — Epic said `onboard scan` should map to \"equivalent audit subcommand\" but audit has no subcommands. Dev agent interpreted as deprecation warning + base audit run. Reasonable decision but AC wording needs tightening in future epics.\n    49→- **Dropped subcommands risk** — `onboard epic` and other old subcommands were silently dropped with no deprecation warning (only `onboard scan` got one). May surprise users who relied on those subcommands.\n    50→- **Old exports removal risk** — `onboard.ts` exported shared state getters (`getLastScanResult`, etc.). Dev agent verified no external consumers before removing. Good diligence.\n    51→\n    52→---\n    53→\n    54→## 3. What Went Well\n    55→\n    56→- **Clean refactoring execution.** 478 lines reduced to 40 lines with a well-structured shared handler extraction (`audit-action.ts`). Both `audit` and `onboard` now share identical logic.\n    57→- **Code review caught real bugs.** The unsafe type assertion was a genuine type safety hole. Catching it before merge prevented potential runtime issues.\n    58→- **No regressions.** 2783 tests passing, zero failures across the full suite after the refactor.\n    59→- **Good dependency verification.** Dev agent checked all removed imports to confirm no other consumers before deleting — library files preserved as required.\n    60→- **Story creation quality.** Session issues log captured ambiguities and risks upfront during create-story phase, enabling informed decisions during implementation.\n    61→\n    62→---\n    63→\n    64→## 4. What Went Wrong\n    65→\n    66→- **Test file size underestimated.** Story estimated 100-150 lines for `onboard.test.ts`; actual was 325 lines (needed compaction to 230). Estimates for test files are consistently too low.\n    67→- **Two code quality issues deferred.** `console.log` usage and the no-op `formatAuditJson()` were flagged but not fixed. Both are minor but accumulate as tech debt.\n    68→- **Session ended with story still in verifying.** The full pipeline (create → dev → review → verify) didn't complete within the session window.\n    69→\n    70→---\n    71→\n    72→## 5. Lessons Learned\n    73→\n    74→### Patterns to Repeat\n    75→\n    76→- **Extracting shared handlers** when aliasing commands. The `audit-action.ts` pattern is clean and reusable for future command aliases.\n    77→- **Session issues log as living document.** Each phase (create-story, dev-story, code-review) contributed entries, creating a complete audit trail. This works.\n    78→- **Code review as bug-catching gate.** The unsafe type assertion would have shipped without review. The review phase paid for itself this session.\n    79→\n    80→### Patterns to Avoid\n    81→\n    82→- **Underestimating test file sizes.** Double the estimate when test files involve multiple mock setups and flag combinations.\n    83→- **Ambiguous ACs referencing non-existent features.** \"Maps to equivalent subcommand\" when no subcommand exists forces dev agents to make judgment calls. Be explicit about deprecation behavior in ACs.\n    84→\n    85→---\n    86→\n    87→## 6. Action Items\n    88→\n    89→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n    90→\n    91→- [ ] Complete verification pass for Story 3-3-onboard-alias (currently `verifying`)\n    92→\n    93→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n    94→\n    95→- [ ] Add `raw()` output utility to `src/lib/output.ts` for pre-formatted string output that shouldn't be prefixed — resolves the `console.log` tech debt in `audit-action.ts`\n    96→- [ ] Review whether `formatAuditJson()` should do actual formatting or be removed as a no-op\n    97→- [ ] Add deprecation warnings for `onboard coverage`, `onboard audit`, `onboard epic` subcommands (currently silently dropped)\n    98→\n    99→### Backlog (Track but Not Urgent)\n   100→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ByFBLT9ziGxFmVXofYDDPj","session_id":"d92c7bcb-37ff-4aa2-841f-ece7fabef071","uuid":"49daaac1-07cd-4b8d-ad7a-c0dc00d69b78","timestamp":"2026-03-21T12:44:58.608Z"}
