{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ByFBLT9ziGxFmVXofYDDPj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Epic 7 retrospective has been written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-7-retrospective.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n- **All 3 stories completed** autonomously in a single day with zero human intervention or circuit breaker trips.\n- **Smallest epic by code volume** — ~60 lines of production changes across 5 files, closing 3 audit compliance gaps (Semgrep, BATS, Dockerfile).\n- **Code review earned its keep again** — caught ~12 issues including 3 HIGH-severity bugs (missing CriticalDependencyError test, bloated .dockerignore sending 85MB+ to Docker daemon, missing ENTRYPOINT).\n- **Dependency registry pattern validated** — scaled from 3 to 5 entries with zero structural changes to the install/check/fallback infrastructure.\n- **0 of 7 Epic 6 action items resolved** — the pattern of carrying forward unresolved retro action items continues for the 4th consecutive epic.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Epic-level problems:**\n- **Epic numbering collision (3rd occurrence):** Three different \"Epic 7\" definitions exist across sprint artifacts (Onboarding Compliance Gaps, OpenSearch Backend, Status & Lifecycle). Flagged in Epic 6 retro, still unresolved. This caused a stale retrospective file that had to be overwritten.\n- **No formal epic definition file:** Epic 7 existed only as story keys in sprint-status.yaml. Second consecutive epic with no planning artifact. Process step being skipped routinely.\n- **Zero retro action items resolved across 4 epics:** Action items are documented, carried, and ignored. The retrospective process produces documentation but does not drive change. This was explicitly called out in the previous sprint's Epic 7 retro (L3) and nothing changed.\n\n**Stories harder than expected:**\n- **7-2 (BATS)** was the most complex — rewriting 14 broken integration tests required understanding the onboard.sh delegation pattern from story 3-3. Still the smallest story in absolute terms.\n- **7-3 (Dockerfile)** hit an unexpected validator limitation (line-by-line parsing can't handle backslash continuations). Required formatting workaround.\n\n**Action items needing immediate attention:**\n- `sprint-state.json` shows story 7-3 as `\"status\": \"review\"` instead of `\"done\"` — needs manual correction if sprint-state accuracy matters for downstream tooling.\n- Semgrep audit gaps showing `undefined` instead of rule message text (flagged in 7-1 session issues) — potential bug in `parseSemgrepOutput`.\n\n**Process improvements to encode in tooling/config:**\n- Batch small (<50 line) compliance-fix stories into a single story with multiple tasks — the 3x pipeline overhead (create/dev/review/verify) for 3 independent 10-line changes is wasteful.\n- Add multi-line continuation support to `dockerfile-validator.ts` before it causes false failures for user projects with standard multi-line Dockerfiles.\n- Story-status sync should be automated in the ralph pipeline — `codeharness sync` exists but is never called. Wire it into the post-verify phase or delete it."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae0360d240d7ab956 (use SendMessage with to: 'ae0360d240d7ab956' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 48105\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 145329</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d92c7bcb-37ff-4aa2-841f-ece7fabef071","uuid":"8c1802fe-b018-45ea-89e2-8394deb4c87d","timestamp":"2026-03-21T12:46:58.139Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /retrospective for Epic 7. All stories are complete. Review the epic's work, extract lessons learned, and produce the retrospective document. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nEpic 7 is \"Onboarding — Compliance Gaps\" with 3 stories:\n- 7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis: Added Semgrep to dependency registry\n- 7-2-fix-bats-runtime-tests: Added BATS to dependency registry and fixed broken tests\n- 7-3-create-dockerfile: Created root Dockerfile for containerized deployment\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Epic-level problems (recurring patterns across stories, process breakdowns)\n- Stories that were harder than expected and why\n- Action items that need immediate attention vs. backlog\n- Process improvements that should be encoded in tooling/config, not just documented\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ae0360d240d7ab956","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Epic 7 retrospective has been written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/epic-7-retrospective.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n- **All 3 stories completed** autonomously in a single day with zero human intervention or circuit breaker trips.\n- **Smallest epic by code volume** — ~60 lines of production changes across 5 files, closing 3 audit compliance gaps (Semgrep, BATS, Dockerfile).\n- **Code review earned its keep again** — caught ~12 issues including 3 HIGH-severity bugs (missing CriticalDependencyError test, bloated .dockerignore sending 85MB+ to Docker daemon, missing ENTRYPOINT).\n- **Dependency registry pattern validated** — scaled from 3 to 5 entries with zero structural changes to the install/check/fallback infrastructure.\n- **0 of 7 Epic 6 action items resolved** — the pattern of carrying forward unresolved retro action items continues for the 4th consecutive epic.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Epic-level problems:**\n- **Epic numbering collision (3rd occurrence):** Three different \"Epic 7\" definitions exist across sprint artifacts (Onboarding Compliance Gaps, OpenSearch Backend, Status & Lifecycle). Flagged in Epic 6 retro, still unresolved. This caused a stale retrospective file that had to be overwritten.\n- **No formal epic definition file:** Epic 7 existed only as story keys in sprint-status.yaml. Second consecutive epic with no planning artifact. Process step being skipped routinely.\n- **Zero retro action items resolved across 4 epics:** Action items are documented, carried, and ignored. The retrospective process produces documentation but does not drive change. This was explicitly called out in the previous sprint's Epic 7 retro (L3) and nothing changed.\n\n**Stories harder than expected:**\n- **7-2 (BATS)** was the most complex — rewriting 14 broken integration tests required understanding the onboard.sh delegation pattern from story 3-3. Still the smallest story in absolute terms.\n- **7-3 (Dockerfile)** hit an unexpected validator limitation (line-by-line parsing can't handle backslash continuations). Required formatting workaround.\n\n**Action items needing immediate attention:**\n- `sprint-state.json` shows story 7-3 as `\"status\": \"review\"` instead of `\"done\"` — needs manual correction if sprint-state accuracy matters for downstream tooling.\n- Semgrep audit gaps showing `undefined` instead of rule message text (flagged in 7-1 session issues) — potential bug in `parseSemgrepOutput`.\n\n**Process improvements to encode in tooling/config:**\n- Batch small (<50 line) compliance-fix stories into a single story with multiple tasks — the 3x pipeline overhead (create/dev/review/verify) for 3 independent 10-line changes is wasteful.\n- Add multi-line continuation support to `dockerfile-validator.ts` before it causes false failures for user projects with standard multi-line Dockerfiles.\n- Story-status sync should be automated in the ralph pipeline — `codeharness sync` exists but is never called. Wire it into the post-verify phase or delete it."}],"totalDurationMs":145329,"totalTokens":48105,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3656,"cache_read_input_tokens":43680,"output_tokens":768,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests"